      • setJsonShardIDKey

        public PostAgent setJsonShardIDKey(java.lang.String shard_id_key)
        Most api has a shard id field in their api docs. Shard id is the 0 based ID of this identity. You do not need to configure this if the identity is not sharded. The default key will be "shard_id".
        Parameters:
        shard_id_key - The new shard id json key.
        Returns:
        PostAgent for chaining.

      • setJsonShardKey

        public PostAgent setJsonShardKey(java.lang.String shard_key)
        Most api has a shard count field in their api docs. Shard count is the total shards this bot have. You do not need to configure this if the identity is not sharded. The default key will be "shard_count".
        Parameters:
        shard_key - The new shard count json key.
        Returns:
        PostAgent for chaining.

      • setJsonServerKey

        public PostAgent setJsonServerKey(java.lang.String server_key)
        Most api has a server count field in their api docs. Server count is the total server this bot have in a shard (if sharded). This key is required to send the status. The default key will be "server_count".
        Parameters:
        server_key - The new server count json key.
        Returns:
        PostAgent for chaining.
